had succeeded General Reynolds. General Gibbon, of the Second Division, assumed command of the corps. These assignments terminated on the evening of July 1. Similar changes in commanders occurred during the battle of the 2nd, when General Hancock was put in command of the Third Corps in addition to that of his own. He was wounded on the 3rd, and Brigadier General William Hays [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0045&node=waro0045%3A5&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=505] was assigned to the command of the corps.</ref> ('''w''')\n<br>\nBG [[John Gibbon]]\n<br>\nBG [[William Hays (general)|William Hays]]\n<br>\nGeneral Headquarters:\n* 6th New York Cavalry, Companies D and K: Cpt Riley Johnson (Escort)\n* [[53rd Pennsylvania Infantry]] , Companies A, B and K: Maj Octavus Bull (Provost Marshal 2nd Corps) <ref>under the command of General Patrick (Provost Marshal General of the Army) during the battle [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A8&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=396]</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John C. Caldwell]][[File:IIcorpsbadge1.png]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Edward E. Cross]] ('''mw''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[H. Boyd McKeen]]\n|\n* [[5th New Hampshire Volunteer Infantry|5th New Hampshire]]: Ltc Charles E. Hapgood, Maj Richard E. Cross\n* [[61st New York Volunteer Infantry|61st New York]]: Ltc [[K. Oscar Broady]]\n* [[81st Pennsylvania Infantry|81st Pennsylvania]]: Col Henry Boyd McKeen, Ltc Amos Stroh\n* [[148th Pennsylvania Infantry|148th Pennsylvania]]: Col H. Boyd McKeen,<ref>Col McKeen was placed in temporary command of the 148th Pennsylvania Infantry because Colonel James Addams Beaver was ill. Col Edward E. Cross believed that Ltc McFarlane was too inexperienced to lead the regiment.</ref> Ltc Robert McFarlane, Maj Robert H. Foster\n|-\n| [[Irish Brigade (US)|2nd Brigade]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Patrick Kelly (Colonel)|Patrick Kelly]]\n|\n* [[28th Massachusetts Infantry regiment|28th Massachusetts]]: Col Richard Byrnes\n* [[63rd New York Infantry]] (2 companies): Ltc Richard C. Bentley ('''w'''), Cpt Thomas Touhy\n* [[U.S. 69th Infantry Regiment|69th New York]] (2 companies): Cpt Richard Moroney ('''w'''), Lt James J. Smith\n* [[88th New York Infantry]] (2 companies): Cpt Denis F. Burke\n* [[116th Pennsylvania Infantry|116th Pennsylvania]] (4 companies): Maj [[St. Clair Augustine Mulholland|St. Clair A. Mulholland]]\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Samuel K. Zook]] ('''mw''' July 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc Charles G. Freudenberg ('''w''' July 2)\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Richard P. Roberts ('''k''')\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLtc John Fraser\n|\n* [[52nd New York Volunteer Infantry|52nd New York]]: Ltc Charles G. Freudenberg ('''w''' July 2), Maj Edward Venuti ('''k'''), Cpt William Scherrer\n* [[57th New York Volunteer Infantry|57th New York]]: Ltc Alford B. Chapman\n* [[66th New York Volunteer Infantry|66th New York]]: Col Orlando H. Morris ('''w'''), Ltc John S. Hammell ('''w'''), Maj Peter A. Nelson\n* [[140th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|140th Pennsylvania]]: Col Richard P. Roberts, Ltc John Fraser, Maj Thomas Rodgers\n|-\n| 4th Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[John R. Brooke]] ('''w''')\n|\n* [[27th Connecticut Infantry Regiment|27th Connecticut]] (2 companies): Ltc Henry C. Merwin ('''k'''), Maj James H. Coburn\n* [[2nd Delaware Volunteer Infantry|2nd Delaware]]: Col William P. Bailey ('''w''' July 2), Ltc David L. Stricker ('''w''' July 2), Cpt Charles H. Christman\n* [[64th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|64th New York]]: Col Daniel G. Bingham ('''w'''), Maj Leman W. Bradley ('''w''')\n* [[53rd Pennsylvania Infantry|53rd Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Richards McMichael\n* [[145th Pennsylvania Infantry|145t