t John W. Fuchs\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj [[Thomas W. Osborn]]\n|\n* 1st New York Light, Battery I: Cpt Michael Wiedrich\n* New York Light, 13th Battery: Lt William Wheeler\n* [[Battery I, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery I]]: Cpt [[Hubert Dilger]]\n* [[Battery K, 1st Ohio Light Artillery|1st Ohio Light, Battery K]]: Cpt Lewis Heckman\n* [[4th U.S. Artillery, Battery G|4th United States, Battery G]]: Lt Bayard Wilkeson ('''mw'''), Lt Eugene A. Bancroft\n|}\n\n===[[XII Corps (Union Army)|XII Corps]]===\nMG [[Henry Slocum|Henry W. Slocum]] <ref>Exercised command of the right wing of the army during a part of the battle. But see Slocum to Meade, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A8&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=783 December 30, 1863] and Meade to Slocum, [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar&cc=moawar&idno=waro0043&node=waro0043%3A8&frm=frameset&view=image&seq=789 February 25, 1864]</ref>\n<br>\nBG [[Alpheus S. Williams]]\n\nProvost Guard:\n* [[10th Maine Volunteer Infantry Regiment|10th Maine Battalion]] (3 companies): Cpt John D. Beardsley\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Division\n! style=\"width:25%;\"|Brigade\n! Regiments and Others\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |\nFirst Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Alpheus S. Williams]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas H. Ruger]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Archibald L. McDougall]]\n|\n* [[5th Connecticut Infantry Regiment|5th Connecticut]]: Col Warren W. Packer\n* [[20th Connecticut Infantry Regiment|20th Connecticut]]: Ltc William B. Wooster, Maj Philo B. Buckingham\n* [[3rd Maryland Volunteer Infantry|3rd Maryland]]: Col Joseph M. Sudsburg, Ltc Gilbert P. Robinson\n* [[123rd New York Volunteer Infantry|123rd New York]]: Ltc James C. Rogers, Cpt Adolphus H. Tanner\n* [[145th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|145th New York]]: Col Edward L. Price\n* [[46th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry|46th Pennsylvania]]: Col James L. Selfridge\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas H. Ruger]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol Silas Colgrove\n|\n* [[27th Indiana Infantry Regiment|27th Indiana]]: Col Silas Colgrove, Ltc [[John R. Fesler]], Maj Theodore F. Colgrove\n* [[2nd Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|2nd Massachusetts]]: Ltc Charles R. Mudge ('''k'''), Maj Charles F. Morse\n* [[13th New Jersey Volunteer Infantry|13th New Jersey]]: Col [[Ezra A. Carman]]\n* [[107th New York Volunteer Infantry|107th New York]]: Col Nirom M. Crane\n* [[3rd Wisconsin Volunteer Infantry Regiment|3rd Wisconsin]]: Col William Hawley, Ltc Martin Flood\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |\nSecond Division\n\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[John W. Geary]]\n| 1st Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[Charles Candy]]\n|\n* [[5th Ohio Infantry|5th Ohio]]: Col John H. Patrick\n* [[7th Ohio Infantry|7th Ohio]]: Col William R. Creighton, Ltc O. J. Crane\n* [[29th Ohio Volunteer Infantry|29th Ohio]]: Cpt Wilbur F. Stevens ('''w'''), Cpt Edward Hayes\n* [[66th Ohio Infantry|66th Ohio]]: Ltc Eugene Powell, Maj Joshua G. Palmer ('''mw''')\n* [[28th Pennsylvania Infantry|28th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt John H. Flynn ('''w''')\n* [[147th Pennsylvania Infantry|147th Pennsylvania]] (8 companies): Ltc [[Ario Pardee, Jr.]], Maj George Harney\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[George A. Cobham, Jr.]]\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Thomas L. Kane]] <ref>Kane returned to the army at Gettysburg on July 2, but he had to share command with Cobham on account of sickness [http://ebooks.library.cornell.edu/cgi/t/text/pageviewer-idx?c=moawar;cc=moawar;idno=waro0043;node=waro0043%3A8;frm=frameset;view=image;seq=868;page=root;size=100]</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\n|\n* [[29th Pennsylvania Infantry|29th Pennsylvania]]: Col William Rickards, Jr., Ltc Samuel M. Zulick\n* [[109th Pennsylvania Infantry|109th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt Frederick L. Gimber\n* [[111th Pennsylvania Infantry|111th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc Thomas M. Walker\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[George S. Greene]] ('''w''')\n|\n* [[60th New York Volunteer Infantry|60th New York]]: Col Abel Godard, Ltc John C. O. Redington\n* [[78th New York Volunteer Infantry|78th New York]]: Ltc Herbert von Hammerstein, Maj William H. Randall ('''w''')\n* [[102nd New York Volunteer Infantry|102nd New York]]: Col James C. Lane ('''w''', July 2), Cpt [[Lewis R. Stegman]]\n* [[137th New York Volunteer Infantry|137th New York]]: Col [[David Ireland (colonel)|David Ireland]], Ltc Koert S. Van Voorhees ('''w''')\n* [[149th New York]]: Ltc Charles B. Randall ('''w''')\n|-\n| ''Reporting directly''\n| Lockwood's Brigade <ref>Unassigned during progress of battle; afterward attached to First Division, as Second Brigade. The command theretofore known as the Second Brigade had previously been consolidated with the First Brigade</ref>\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nBG [[Henry H. Lockwood]]\n|\n* [[1st Maryland Infantry, Potomac Home Brigade|1st Maryland, Potomac Home Brigade]]: Col William P. Maulsby\n* [[1st Regiment Eastern Shore Maryland Volunteer Infantry|1st Maryland, Eastern Shore]]: Col James Wallace\n* [[150th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|150th New York]]: Col [[John H. Ketcham]], Ltc Charles G. Bartlett, Maj [[Alfred Baker Smith]]\n|-\n|\n| Artillery Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nLt [[Edward D. Muhlenberg]]\n|\n* 1st New York Light, Battery M: Lt [[Charles E. Winegar]]\n* [[Independent Battery E, Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Pennsylvania Light, Battery E]]: Lt Charles A. Atwell\n* 4th United States, Battery F: Lt [[Sylvanus T. Rugg]]\n* [[5th U.S. Artillery, Battery K|5th United States, Battery K]]: Lt David H. Kinzie\n|}\n\n===[[Cavalry Corps (Union Army)|Cavalry Corps]]===\nMG [[Alfred Pleasonton]]\n\nHeadquarter Guards:\n* [[1st Ohio Cavalry]], Company A: Cpt Noah Jones (Second Division)\n* [[1st Ohio Cavalry]], Company C: Cpt Samuel N. Stanford (Third Division)\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! styl