rv}}\n* {{cite book |title=[[American on Purpose]]: The Improbable Adventures of an Unlikely Patriot |publisher=[[HarperCollins]] |first=Craig |last=Ferguson |year=2009 |isbn=978-0-06-171954-7 |ref=harv}}\n*Ferguson, Craig (2019). ''Riding the Elephant: A Memoir of Altercations, Humiliations, Hallucinations, and Observations.'' [[Penguin Group]].\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0272401}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-media}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Craig Kilborn]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Host of ''[[The Late Late Show (CBS TV series)|The Late Late Show]]''|years=2005\u20132014}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[James Corden]]}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Les Stroud]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=Host of [[Shark Week]]|years=2010}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Andy Samberg]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Daytime Emmy Award Outstanding Game Show Host}}\n{{The Late Late Show (CBS TV series)}}\n\n{{Subject bar|portal1=Biography|portal2=Comedy|portal3=Scotland|portal4=Television |portal5=United States|commons=yes|commons-search=Category:Craig Ferguson|q=yes|d=yes|d-search=Q72867}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferguson, Craig}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American novelists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Scottish male actors]]\n[[Category:Aviators from California]]\n[[Category:American game show hosts]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male novelists]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American male video game actors]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:American memoirists]]\n[[Category:American male screenwriters]]\n[[Category:American people of Scottish descent]]\n[[Category:American stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:American television talk show hosts]]\n[[Category:Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Game Show Host winners]]\n[[Category:The Late Late Show with Craig Ferguson]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Glasgow]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Male actors from New York City]]\n[[Category:Peabody Award winners]]\n[[Category:People from Cumbernauld]]\n[[Category:Scottish emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Scottish expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Scottish game show hosts]]\n[[Category:Scottish stand-up comedians]]\n[[Category:Scottish television talk show hosts]]\n[[Category:Scottish male film actors]]\n[[Category:Scottish male television actors]]\n[[Category:Scottish male video game actors]]\n[[Category:Scottish male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Late night television talk show hosts]]\n[[Category:Burroughs Corporation people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century Scottish novelists]]\n[[Category:American male comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century American comedians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Scottish male actors]]\n[[Category:Comedians from Glasgow]]\n[[Category:20th-century Scottish comedians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Scottish comedians]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from California]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:Novelists from New York (state)]]\n[[Category:21st-century American non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:People with acquired American citizenship]]\n", "name_user": "Insta is Lush Picstagram", "label": "safe", "comment": "I made sure the people knew what his accomplishments were", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Craig_Ferguson"}
{"title_page": "GTPBP4", "text_new": "{{Infobox_gene}}\n'''Nucleolar GTP-binding protein 1''' is a [[protein]] that in humans is encoded by the ''GTPBP4'' [[gene]].<ref name=\"pmid11316846\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Laping NJ, Olson BA, Zhu Y | title = Identification of a novel nuclear guanosine triphosphate-binding protein differentially expressed in renal disease | journal = J Am Soc Nephrol | volume = 12 | issue = 5 | pages = 883\u201390 |date=Apr 2001 | pmid = 11316846 | pmc =  | doi =  }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: GTPBP4 GTP binding protein 4| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=23560| accessdate = }}</ref>\n\n[[GTPase|GTPases]] function as molecular switches that can flip between two states: active, when GTP is bound, and inactive, when GDP is bound. 'Active' usually means that the molecule acts as a signal to trigger other events in the cell. When an extracellular ligand binds to a [[G protein-coupled receptor]], the receptor changes its conformation and switches on the trimeric G proteins that associate with it by causing them to eject their GDP and replace it with GTP. The switch is turned off when the G protein hydrolyzes its own bound GTP, converting it back to GDP. But before that occurs, the active protein has an opportunity to diffuse away from the receptor and deliver its message for a prolonged period to its downstream target.<ref name=\"entrez\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin | 2}}\n*{{cite journal  |vauthors=Maruyama K, Sugano S |title=Oligo-capping: a simple method to replace the cap structure of eukaryotic mRNAs with oligoribonucleotides. |journal=Gene |volume=138 |issue= 1\u20132 |pages= 171\u20134 |year= 1994 |pmid= 8125298 |doi=10.1016/0378-1119(94)90802-8  }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Suzuki Y, Yoshitomo-Nakagawa K, Maruyama K, etal |title=Construction and characterization of a full length-enriched and a 5'-end-enriched cDNA library. |journal=Gene |volume=200 |issue= 1\u20132 |pages= 149\u201356 |year= 1997 |pmid= 9373149 |doi=10.1016/S0378-1119(97)00411-3  }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Scherl A, Cout\u00e9 Y, D\u00e9on C, etal |title=Functional proteomic analysis of human nucleolus. |journal=Mol. Biol. Cell |volume=13 |issue= 11 |pages= 4100\u20139 |year= 2003 |pmid= 12429849 |doi= 10.1091/mbc.E02-05-0271  | pmc=133617 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Strausberg RL, Feingold EA, Grouse LH, etal |title=Generation and initial analysis of more than 15,000 full-length human and mouse cDNA sequences. |journal=Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. |volume=99 |issue= 26 |pages= 16899\u2013903 |year= 2003 |pmid= 12477932 |doi= 10.1073/pnas.242603899  | pmc=139241 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Ota T, Suzuki Y, Nishikawa T, etal |title=Complete sequencing and characterization of 21,243 full-length human cDNAs. |journal=Nat. Genet. |volume=36 |issue= 1 |pages= 40\u20135 |year= 2004 |pmid= 14702039 |doi= 10.1038/ng1285 |doi-access= free }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Gerhard DS, Wagner L, Feingold EA, etal |title=The status, quality, and expansion of the NIH full-length cDNA project: the Mammalian Gene Collection (MGC). |journal=Genome Res. |volume=14 |issue= 10B |pages= 2121\u20137 |year= 2004 |pmid= 15489334 |doi= 10.1101/gr.2596504  | pmc=528928 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Olsen JV, Blagoev B, Gnad F, etal |title=Global, in vivo, and site-specific phosphorylation dynamics in signaling networks. |journal=Cell |volume=127 |issue= 3 |pages= 635\u201348 |year= 2006 |pmid= 17081983 |doi= 10.1016/j.cell.2006.09.026 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Lee H, Kim D, Dan HC, etal |title=Identification and characterization of putative tumor suppressor NGB, a GTP-binding protein that interacts with the neurofibromatosis 2 protein. |journal=Mol. Cell. Biol. |volume=27 |issue= 6 |pages= 2103\u201319 |year= 2007 |pmid= 17210637 |doi= 10.1128/MCB.00572-06  | pmc=1820506 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Ewing RM, Chu P, Elisma F, etal |title=Large-scale mapping of human protein-protein interactions by mass spectrometry. |journal=Mol. Syst. Biol. |volume=3 |issue=  1|pages= 89 |year= 2007 |pmid= 17353931 |doi= 10.1038/msb4100134  | pmc=1847948 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n\n{{gene-10-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox_gene}}\n'''Nucleolar GTP-binding protein 1''' is a [[protein]] that in humans is encoded by the ''GTPBP4'' [[gene]].<ref name=\"pmid11316846\">{{cite journal |vauthors=Laping NJ, Olson BA, Zhu Y | title = Identification of a novel nuclear guanosine triphosphate-binding protein differentially expressed in renal disease | journal = J Am Soc Nephrol | volume = 12 | issue = 5 | pages = 883\u201390 |date=Apr 2001 | pmid = 11316846 | pmc =  | doi =  }}</ref><ref name=\"entrez\">{{cite web | title = Entrez Gene: GTPBP4 GTP binding protein 4| url = https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=gene&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=23560| accessdate = }}</ref>\n\n[[GTPase|GTPases]] function as molecular switches that can flip between two states: active, when GTP is bound, and inactive, when GDP is bound. 'Active' sually means that the molecule acts as a signal to trigger other events in the cell. When an extracellular ligand binds to a [[G protein-coupled receptor]], the receptor changes its conformation and switches on the trimeric G proteins that associate with it by causing them to eject their GDP and replace it with GTP. The switch is turned off when the G protein hydrolyzes its own bound GTP, converting it back to GDP. But before that occurs, the active protein has an opportunity to diffuse away from the receptor and deliver its message for a prolonged period to its downstream target.<ref name=\"entrez\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin | 2}}\n*{{cite journal  |vauthors=Maruyama K, Sugano S |title=Oligo-capping: a simple method to replace the cap structure of eukaryotic mRNAs with oligoribonucleotides. |journal=Gene |volume=138 |issue= 1\u20132 |pages= 171\u20134 |year= 1994 |pmid= 8125298 |doi=10.1016/0378-1119(94)90802-8  }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Suzuki Y, Yoshitomo-Nakagawa K, Maruyama K, etal |title=Construction and characterization of a full length-enriched and a 5'-end-enriched cDNA library. |journal=Gene |volume=200 |issue= 1\u20132 |pages= 149\u201356 |year= 1997 |pmid= 9373149 |doi=10.1016/S0378-1119(97)00411-3  }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Scherl A, Cout\u00e9 Y, D\u00e9on C, etal |title=Functional proteomic analysis of human nucleolus. |journal=Mol. Biol. Cell |volume=13 |issue= 11 |pages= 4100\u20139 |year= 2003 |pmid= 12429849 |doi= 10.1091/mbc.E02-05-0271  | pmc=133617 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Strausberg RL, Feingold EA, Grouse LH, etal |title=Generation and initial analysis of more than 15,000 full-length human and mouse cDNA sequences. |journal=Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. |volume=99 |issue= 26 |pages= 16899\u2013903 |year= 2003 |pmid= 12477932 |doi= 10.1073/pnas.242603899  | pmc=139241 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Ota T, Suzuki Y, Nishikawa T, etal |title=Complete sequencing and characterization of 21,243 full-length human cDNAs. |journal=Nat. Genet. |volume=36 |issue= 1 |pages= 40\u20135 |year= 2004 |pmid= 14702039 |doi= 10.1038/ng1285 |doi-access= free }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Gerhard DS, Wagner L, Feingold EA, etal |title=The status, quality, and expansion of the NIH full-length cDNA project: the Mammalian Gene Collection (MGC). |journal=Genome Res. |volume=14 |issue= 10B |pages= 2121\u20137 |year= 2004 |pmid= 15489334 |doi= 10.1101/gr.2596504  | pmc=528928 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Olsen JV, Blagoev B, Gnad F, etal |title=Global, in vivo, and site-specific phosphorylation dynamics in signaling networks. |journal=Cell |volume=127 |issue= 3 |pages= 635\u201348 |year= 2006 |pmid= 17081983 |doi= 10.1016/j.cell.2006.09.026 }}\n*{{cite journal   |vauthors=Lee H, Kim D, Dan HC, etal |title=Identification and characterization of putative tumor suppress